cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.DB 

This paper is about multimedia near duplicate detection, which involves the use of multimedia technologies and retrieval systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses hashing methods, which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases).
